{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01PQTrarxsW6e84YWEZYCqB9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01B5YPwJhRN8ajZZHBueQExd","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/HERB ROASTED PORK WITH MUSHROOMS : PORK WITH CARAMELIZED ONIONS (VARIATION).generated.22.txt","content":"HERB ROASTED PORK WITH MUSHROOMS : PORK WITH CARAMELIZED ONIONS (VARIATION)\n\nMAIN RECIPE: HERB ROASTED PORK WITH MUSHROOMS\n\nIngredients:\n\n1.2kg pork shoulder or leg roast\n500g mixed mushrooms (cremini, portobello, oyster), quartered\n8 cloves garlic, crushed\n4 sprigs fresh rosemary\n4 sprigs fresh thyme\n3 tbsp olive oil\n200ml white wine\n300ml chicken or pork stock\n2 bay leaves\nsalt and pepper to taste\n2 tbsp Dijon mustard\n\nInstructions:\n\n1. Preheat oven to 180°C.\n2. Mix olive oil, mustard, crushed garlic, rosemary, thyme, salt, and pepper.\n3. Rub generously all over the pork roast.\n4. Heat a large roasting pan over medium-high heat. Brown the roast on all sides, about 10 minutes total.\n5. Remove roast and set aside.\n6. In the same pan, sauté mushrooms until golden, 5-7 minutes. Remove and set aside.\n7. Deglaze pan with white wine, scraping up browned bits.\n8. Add stock, bay leaves, and return roast and mushrooms.\n9. Cover with foil and roast for 1.5-2 hours until meat is tender (internal temp 70°C).\n10. Let rest 15 minutes before carving. Serve with pan juices.\n\n---\n\nVARIATION: PORK WITH CARAMELIZED ONIONS\n\nSubstitute mushrooms with:\n6 large onions, sliced into half-moons\n2 tbsp brown sugar\n1 tbsp balsamic vinegar\n\nMethod:\n1. Follow main recipe steps 1-5.\n2. In the roasting pan, cook sliced onions with brown sugar and salt over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until deeply caramelized (20-25 minutes).\n3. Add balsamic vinegar, stir well.\n4. Return roast to pan, add stock and bay leaves, proceed with roasting as in main recipe.\n5. The onions will collapse into a rich, jammy accompaniment to the pork.\n\nBoth versions serve 6-8 people. Pair with roasted potatoes or creamed cauliflower.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":679,"cache_read_input_tokens":110395,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":679},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"34e3cc89-b327-406a-aaab-3cc3ab4ee748","uuid":"6719e15f-001b-492c-a675-c8e932fed631"}
