 sliced onions with brown sugar and salt over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until deeply caramelized (20-25 minutes).\n3. Add balsamic vinegar, stir well.\n4. Return roast to pan, add stock and bay leaves, proceed with roasting as in main recipe.\n5. The onions will collapse into a rich, jammy accompaniment to the pork.\n\nBoth versions serve 6-8 people. Pair with roasted potatoes or creamed cauliflower.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
